rComments: I took APS510 Innovative Technologies and Organizations in Global Energy Systems in Fall 2019 with Dr. Mohee. The course was quite informative and the workload is reasonable. Dr. Mohee laid out his expectations for the course very clearly throughout the semester including for the midterm and final. The invited guest lecturers were amazing. Thanks!

Several Industry guest speakers in this class, therefore a great professional networking for students in this class which is helpful to get summer coop job. Very organized course notes. Really helpful to students. He replied to students' emails very quickly. He was always available to students outside of the class. Fair final exam.
Prof. Mohee is one of the best profs I've had in my entire undergrad. He genuinely cares for his students.
I really like this professor and clearly everyone else which can be seen from all the positive comments that could be read here

He brought more of an industry focus to the course, previous years were largely theoretical and too textbook focused. Very approachable prof during office hours and via email, and gives great career advice. Was a bit disorganized, though it was his first time teaching the course; but he was open to feedback and was passionate about the field.

Such an excellent professor. He really cares about his students and always there for them. Lecture notes more than enough barely opened the textbook. I really wish he teaches me again. Best prof out there!!!!
The besttt proff ever I have taken with so farr!! God bless him I really wish I can take the course one more time with him!!

Professor Mohee was very helpful in explaining the course and always excepted questions from students. He made himself regularly available for extra help and was more than fair with preparing us for our final exam.

Tbh, regardless of the fact that he replies to emails quickly, he isnt a good professor. I used to feel bad about students complaining about him 24/7 until I paid full attention in class and realized that he really isnt a good professor. Maybe with more practice he can become better. Kinda confused by all these comments bc no one actually liked him

The best prof in UofT I wish he teaches us again. Never missed his lectures. The textbook was useless in this course his explanations were more than enough and lecture slides. Highly esteemed prof much love sir Faizul. He always shows care to his students. Best prof in the world.
With no doubt best Professor in UofT. Explanation is simply phenomenal. I wish he teaches me in 3rd and 4th year. Make sure to LISTEN to his advice and lectures.

Great Professor, inspired me a lot in engineering. Guaranteed you'll love the course and the professor even more. Explains the course with lots of details. Slides are the best ever. Attend classes, listen to advice and you'll do great. Make sure to study hard. The professor is very helpful also outside of class. GREATEST PROF EVER!!!

Professor Mohee taught the second half of MIE270. He truly cares about all of his students and enjoys teaching. Very accessible - answered all questions (in class, after class, office hours). He brought in very interesting guest speakers and material samples relevant to the course material. Professional, smart and offers practical advice.

I am now in my second year he is really one of the best profs Ive ever met in my life. He is so helpful and cares too much about his students. I barely opened the textbook his lecture slides were amazing and enough to study from. He was always there for his students during office hours. We are lucky to have such an amazing professor!God bless him

Prof. Mohee really cares for his students. He is one of the best profs I've had in my entire undergrad so far. The students who attended his classes, followed his course notes and example problems; and actually studied little bit must have done really well in this course.

His lecture slides are good. You dont really need to read the book along with them and he responds to emails quite fast. However, he could have provided us with the equations and constants during the exam. Mats. science isnt supposed to be a course where you memorize everything, rather you should be tested on your ability to apply your knowledge.

Dr. Mohee was often available for questions outside of class and had more office hours close to exam time was great. He would also email back extremely quickly if you had a question: very accessible lecturer. He also brought in great guest speakers. Super interesting material and very knowledgeable.

Prof. Mohee is one of the best profs I've had in my entire undergrad. He genuinely cares for his students. He tries to make the classes engaged by showing physical samples, showing videos, guest lectures, solving problems in board. Would take his classes again for sure. Very helpful during his office hours. Several solved problems in course note.

Very organized course notes. Very helpful to students. He replied to students' emails very quickly every time. He was always available to students outside of the class during his office hours. did not need to buy any extra book for his course. Several guest speakers from industry.

showed lots of materials and physical prototypes in class to explain different topics several guest speakers from industry, one speaker from Bombardier, one speaker from General Motors, one from MTO. He was always very quick in replying emails from studets He was always available outside of class to explain topics to students individually

AWFUL. His slides are wrong. Does not teach. Don't waste your time going to lecture just learn the material on your own time. So unorganized.
